    <title>Home Made Hoisin Sauce</title>
    <filename>home_made_hoisin_sauce.xml</filename>

    <comment>c/o blessherheartyall With cazzie tweaks </comment>
    <thumbnail>../images/placeholder.png</thumbnail>
    <image></image>
    <category></category>
    <yield></yield>
    <prepTime></prepTime>
    <cookTime></cookTime>
    


    <diet>GlutenFree</diet>

    <ingredient>8 TBSP Gluten Free Soy Sauce</ingredient>
    <ingredient>5 TBSP peanut butter </ingredient>
    <ingredient>3 TBSP honey</ingredient>
    <ingredient>1/4 cup fresh green onions chopped </ingredient>
    <ingredient>1/2 TBSP chilli flakes</ingredient>
    <ingredient>4 teasp rice wine vinegar</ingredient>
    <ingredient>1 TBSP garlic powder </ingredient>
    <ingredient>3 teaspoons sesame oil</ingredient>
    <ingredient>1 TBSP chilli paste</ingredient>

    <step>
Place all ingredients in a small sauce pan and cook for about five minutes on low or until all ingredients combined and thickened slightly. Store in airtight container.
    </step>
</recipe>